IMAGES 

Rounded Corners .rounded
Circular .rounded-circle
Thumbnail .img-thumbnail

Aligning image to right : .float-right
Aligning image to left : .float-left
Aligning image to center : .mx-auto(margin auto) and .d-block(display block)

Responsive image to manage size .img-fluid

ALERTS

use .alert

for colored alerts 
.alert .alert-success
.alert .alert-danger
.alert .alert-primary
.alert .alert-warning
.alert .alert-secondary
.alert .alert-dark
.alert .alert-info

for making links in the alert of same color use .alert-link (for the 'a' tag)

DISMISSABLE OR CLOSING ALERTS !
we make a div with classes alert , alert-success(for color) , alert-dismissible
requires js

    <div class="alert alert-success alert-dismissible fade show">
      <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert">&times;</button>
      <strong>Success</strong> alert <a href="#" class="alert-link">Click Here !</a> 
    </div>

for animations we used fade show

BUTTONS IN BOOTSTRAP

use classes btn and for color use 

btn btn-success
btn btn-primary
btn btn-danger
btn btn-warning
btn btn-danger
btn btn-dark and so on...
<button type = "button" class="btn btn-primary"></button>

OUTLINES
 use btn btn-outline-primary

BUTTON SIZES 

btn btn-primary btn-lg (large)
btn btn-primary btn-sm (small)

use .btn-block for full width button

ACTIVE DISABLED 
use .active and .disabled

SPINNERS TO BUTTONS

use .spinner-border , .spinner-border-sm

BUTTON GROUP

.btn-group

for vertical groups 

.btn-group-vertical

DROPDOWNS WITH BUTTONS


classes in button : .btn .btn-primary .dropdown-toggle 
extra attribute : data-toggle="dropdown"

then make a div with class .dropdown-menu

and include 'a' elements with class .dropdown-item


BADGES

These are used to provide extra info about a text 

use span and use class .badge for badge 

and alongside with .badge use
.badge-primary
.badge-secondary
.badge-success
.badge-warning
.badge-danger
.badge-info
.badge-dark

for different colors

Example : <h1>Sample heading <span class="badge badge-info">new</span></h1>

for round badges use .badge-pill

Example : <h1>Sample heading <span class="badge badge-pill badge-info">new</span></h1>

badge inside elements 

<button class="btn btn-info">Message <span class="badge badge-light">5</span></button>


PROGRESS BAR 

add .progress  to the class of containing element and class .progress-bar to child

and inside child element use style and then width property to set the progress bar

Striped progress add .progress-bar-striped

Animated bar : .progress-bar .progress-bar-striped .progress-bar-animated

PAGINATION 

use ul for this 
use .pagination class in ul
use .page-item class in li
use .page-link class in anchor tag in li 
use .active class in li to highlight the respective page link
use .disabled to make link unclickable
use .pagination-lg for larger or pagination-sm for smaller boxes in ul
use .justify-content-center for center alignment and .justify-content-end for right aligned


BREAD CRUMBS 

other type for pagination

use .breadcrumb in ul
use .breadcrumb-item in li

LISTGROUPS

use .list-group in ul 
use .list-group-item in li
use .active for active state

Linked List Group

use .list-group-item in a tag and .list-group-item-action for hover

use .diabled for unclickable links

use .list-group-flush for removing borders

use .list-group-item-info etc for colors 


BOOTSTRAP CARDS

.card class in containing element 
.card-body for content
.card-header for header
.card-footer for footer
.card-title to add card title to headings
.card-text in p tag for text 
.card-link for card links
.card-img-top or card-img-bottom for images
.card-img-overlay for making text written over the image
.card-columns for grid like arramgements of card (pinterest example)
.card-deck for grid card layout of equal height and width
.card-group :: same as card-deeck with left and right margins













































































































































































